      <heading>Sun Jul 22 (Aidan)      :: Some More Stuff</heading>
      <slot>3</slot>
      <level>199</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
Dice results for Taveren are 4 to 6. Everyone else is 1 to 6.

Practices add 30 plus a random number from 0 to your UNMODIFIED int plus a
 random number from 0 to your UNMODIFIED wis. Then divide by 2. That's right
 folks, stat eq does not affect practicing. It does affect how many pracs you
 get when you gain a level, though. Oh, and if you are ta'veren, it adds a 
random number from -25 to +25.

(30 + random(0, unmodified int) +random(0, unmodified wis))/2
or, anywhere from 15 at the minimum to 45 at the maximum.

So, those who raise their stats all the way to 30 with trains average
30 per practice and those like me who have natural stats at 4 and use
just loads of stat eq average 17 or so per practice. Since everyone
uses practices to get to 70% anyway, that means the difference is not
that great. Max stats causes an average of 61% after 2 pracs. So they
still have to spend a third to get to 70. Takes me 4 pracs to get to
69 on average. Sometimes it takes it to 70. Either way, takes ten 
skills to cost me an extra train and 46 or so trains to raise my stat
to 30.. 92 to raise both int and wise to 30.. So, it would take around
920 skills for it to average out.

Oh, not counting the different skills that affect regen, Soldier and
Adventurer regain hitpoints 30% faster and Wilders and Channelers
regain mana 30% faster. Yes, a sparked wisdom is totally screwed.

</text>
