      <text>I've been away for a while, so to these postings there shall come a
responce after a little time. To those that I looked at, most of them
were, technically, just ones left over from when Newbiegoto couldn't
be changed without the help of a Coder. But since I, or any Builder
could add Newbiegoto flags, I changed those that were redundant.
The Quest Skills and the Mailing place are now gone, however all the rest
shall stay. There are many reasons for this, so I shall state them here.

1) Lugard - If you had actually gone there you would note that its
the Taxi Stop just outside of Caemlyn. Since newbies really can't afford
to cart everywhere, they can learn the old fashioned way and use the Taxi
system like everyone did once. Hopefully.

2) Deven Ride is a great place that most newbies can run around and kill
some small things for somewhat good gold and experience. As well, its a
good replacement for Caemlyn when one gets tired of that.

3) You might not see many newbies wanting to repair something, but they
do like to repair things. Even if they never use it, it is always there
-for- them if they ever need to.

4) See Deven Ride, but its good for level 20+ newbies to play in.

Kale
</text>
